5335

img elements must have an accessible name.
Add an alt attribute describing the image, which screen readers voice instead of the image. Spacer images and purely decorative images should use alt="". Do not use alt text containing only spaces since that's voiced as an unlabeled image.

Impact on users:

  • NVDA 2019.2 Chrome 79 Windows 10 Reading: Image unlabeled.
  • NVDA 2019.2 FF68 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • NVDA 2019.2 IE11 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • NVDA 2018.4 Chrome 73 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • NVDA 2018.4 FF60 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • NVDA 2018.4 IE11 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • JAWS 2019.1912.1 Chrome 79 Windows 10 Reading: Image unlabeled.
  • JAWS 2019.1912.1 FF68 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • JAWS 2019.1912.1 IE11 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • JAWS 2018.1811.2 Chrome 73 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • JAWS 2018.1811.2 FF60 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • JAWS 2018.1811.2 IE11 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • VoiceOver macOS 10.14 Safari 13.0 macOS 10.14.6 Reading: Image filename read out.
  • VoiceOver macOS 10.13 Safari 12.1 macOS 10.13.6 Reading: Image filename read out.

img elements must have an accessible name.
Add an alt attribute describing the image, which screen readers voice instead of the image. Spacer images and purely decorative images should use alt="". Do not use alt text containing only spaces since that's voiced as an unlabeled image.

Impact on users:

  • NVDA 2019.2 Chrome 79 Windows 10 Reading: Image unlabeled.
  • NVDA 2019.2 FF68 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • NVDA 2019.2 IE11 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • NVDA 2018.4 Chrome 73 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • NVDA 2018.4 FF60 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • NVDA 2018.4 IE11 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • JAWS 2019.1912.1 Chrome 79 Windows 10 Reading: Image unlabeled.
  • JAWS 2019.1912.1 FF68 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • JAWS 2019.1912.1 IE11 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • JAWS 2018.1811.2 Chrome 73 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • JAWS 2018.1811.2 FF60 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • JAWS 2018.1811.2 IE11 Windows 10 Reading: Image ignored.
  • VoiceOver macOS 10.14 Safari 13.0 macOS 10.14.6 Reading: Image filename read out.
  • VoiceOver macOS 10.13 Safari 12.1 macOS 10.13.6 Reading: Image filename read out.
  • VoiceOver macOS 10.12 Safari 10.1.2 macOS 10.12.6 Reading: Image filename read out.
  • VoiceOver iOS 12.4 Safari iOS 12.4 iOS 12.4.1 Touch: Image filename read out.
  • VoiceOver iOS 11.4 Safari iOS 11.4 iOS 11.4.1 Touch: Image filename read out.
  • VoiceOver iOS 10.3 Safari iOS 10.3 iOS 10.3 Touch: Image filename read out.

5593 <h3 class="subHdr">Engineered for Beautiful Durability</h3>

5594 <p class="bodyCopy">Dekton is a combination of glass, porcelain, quartz, and other natural materials. Using advanced technology along with intense heat and pressure, the result is a product that has all the beauty of natural stone, but with stronger properties. Dekton has a high resistance to heat, scratches, stains, freezing, and thawing. The surface is non-porous, meaning there's little to no water absorption. The engineering process results in larger pieces, providing you with a countertop that doesn't require joints or seams. It's available in three textures. XGloss features a highly polished sheen. UItratexture provides a natural look, capturing the beauty of textures such as wood, slate, or marble. Ultramatte has a matte finish for a softer appearance. Overall, Dekton is a great material to use indoors or outdoors, including kitchens, bathrooms, islands, and bar tops.</p>

For purely decorative images and spacers use alt='', for images of text use the text, and for other images use a description of the image.

Impact on users:

  • JAWS : Reads out placeholder text, instead of a useful image description.
  • NVDA : Reads out placeholder text, instead of a useful image description.
  • VoiceOver : Reads out placeholder text, instead of a useful image description.

6226 <h3 class="subHdr">Supercharged Quartz</h3>

6227 <p class="bodyCopy">Silestone is crafted from over 94% natural quartz to create a gorgeous, non-porous countertop option. Since quartz is one of the most sturdy materials around, Silestone is resistant to stains from coffee, wine, olive oil, makeup, and other substances that tend to mar surfaces. On top of over 90 colors, there are also three unique textures to choose from. Go with Polished for richer, high-shine colors. Select Volcano for a rugged finish that adds notes of texture. Opt for Suede for a velvety look thats also soft and smooth to the touch. With its tough composition, Silestone is a great option for both kitchens and bathrooms.</p>

6842 <h3 class="subHdr">Gorgeous Granite</h3>

6843 <p class="bodyCopy">Sensa is different from other granites because it features a specialized protective coating that provides stain resistance as well as protection against UV rays. This coating is also Greenguard certified, meaning its safe for direct contact with food. Each slab is unique, naturally sourced with special attention to finding the most beautiful colors and veining so you have a one-of-a-kind style in your home. Cleaning is as easy as using water and a non-abrasive soap, keeping worktops germ-free and beautiful. Sensa combines the benefits of natural stone with technology to make it more durable.</p>

7433 <h3 class="subHdr">Highly Personalized For Your Space</h3>

7434 <p class="bodyCopy">The Natural Stone collection features a variety of materials including marble, travertine, granite, limestone, and more. These slabs are sourced from around the world to provide gorgeous, completely natural surfaces to enhance the beauty of your home. Each type of stone and slab has its own unique characteristics, strengths, and features. All are fire and heat resistant, as well as resistant to UV rays which keeps the coloring consistent over time. Natural Stone brings a unique touch that can't be replicated.</p>

8031 <span class="identifier-plugin " id="countertop-types-row">

8032 <div class="styles-plugin-outer custom-outer-style-ROW-f-b-bbd-fd-fbffb">

8033 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-ROW-f-b-bbd-fd-fbffb">

8034 <div class="Row-module_global__1T17H merce-row-container">

8035 <div class="Layout-module_row__3IzXF merce-row">

8036 <div class="Layout-module_omnimerse-column-sm-12__29AUW Layout-module_marginTopOnSmall__2rO47 merce-column">

8037 <div>

8038 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-COLUMN-adfe-a-f-bfe-aad">

8039 <div class="merce-column-container">

8040 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-b-d-ba--bafef">

8041 <div>

8042 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

8043 <div>

8044 <h2 class="hdr normal textCenter" style="text-align: center;">What Types of Countertops Are There?</h2>

8045 <p style="text-align: center;">There are quite a few options for countertops. Each has their pros and cons, but take a look and see which you gravitate to most.</p>

8046 </div>

8047 </div>

8048 </div>

8049 </div>

8050 <div>

8051 <div class="styles-plugin-outer custom-outer-style-ROW-afb-fc-b-abe-eeee">

8052 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-ROW-afb-fc-b-abe-eeee">

8053 <div class="Row-module_global__1T17H merce-row-container">

8054 <div class="Layout-module_row__3IzXF merce-row">

8055 <div class="Layout-module_omnimerse-column-sm-4__3eiub Layout-module_marginTopOnSmall__2rO47 merce-column">

8056 <div>

8057 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-COLUMN-eed-da-d-bb-cbcc">

8058 <div class="merce-column-container">

8059 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK--ac-eb-db-abeedf">

8060 <div>

8061 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

8062 <div>

8063 <p class="subHdr">Quartz</p>

8064 </div>

8065 </div>

8066 </div>

8067 </div>

8068 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-SINGLE_IMAGE-a-eb--b-abfacddfc">

8069 <div class="SingleImage-module_singleImage__3fWXf a-eb--b-abfacddfc-singleImageAlignment">

8070 <img title="quartz" class="a-eb--b-abfacddfc-image" alt="quartz" src="https://img.vevano.com/iLWBgZKjoq7R06hPLNWIV8yayPJMZqW-2AN2rECJD3s/rs:fill:0:132/q:80/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdG9yYWdlLmdvb2dsZWFwaXMuY29tL3ZldmFuby1hc3NldHMvY29zZW50aW5vL2NvdW50ZXJ0b3BRdWFydHouanBn">

8071 </div>

8072 </div>

8073 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-ada-f--ab-fedf">

8074 <div>

8075 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

8076 <div>

8077 <p class="bodyCopy">Technically an engineered stone, quartz combines with other natural materials to create an incredibly sturdy countertop. Thanks to its resilience, its popularity is growing in both kitchens and bathrooms. Unlike granite, quartz is a non-porous surface, giving it a natural resistance to staining, scratches, and heat without the need for sealant. Thanks to a bonding process that involves high temperatures and intense pressure, quartz is also impact resistant.</p>

8078 </div>

8079 </div>

8080 </div>

8081 </div>

8082 </div>

8083 </div>

8084 </div>

8085 </div>

8086 <div class="Layout-module_omnimerse-column-sm-4__3eiub Layout-module_marginTopOnSmall__2rO47 merce-column">

8087 <div>

8088 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-COLUMN-dbfbffa-b-f-cd-caceb">

8089 <div class="merce-column-container">

8090 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-cea-faf-a-ae-fccfcfa">

8091 <div>

8092 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

8093 <div>

8094 <p class="subHdr">Granite</p>

8095 </div>

8096 </div>

8097 </div>

8098 </div>

8099 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-SINGLE_IMAGE-bbfc--d-ae-cfbfa">

8100 <div class="SingleImage-module_singleImage__3fWXf bbfc--d-ae-cfbfa-singleImageAlignment">

8101 <img title="granite" class="bbfc--d-ae-cfbfa-image" alt="granite" src="https://img.vevano.com/X-mQpdGSRVyUJ6fpVsFl0KgbqStUv9mNdJxqWYuUjiU/rs:fill:0:132/q:80/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdG9yYWdlLmdvb2dsZWFwaXMuY29tL3ZldmFuby1hc3NldHMvY29zZW50aW5vL2NvdW50ZXJ0b3BHcmFuaXRlLmpwZw">

8102 </div>

8103 </div>

8104 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-d-ac--ac-effa">

8105 <div>

8106 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

8107 <div>

8108 <p class="bodyCopy">A natural stone known for both beauty and durability, granite is a popular choice for countertops in kitchens or bathrooms. Its durable, resistant to both heat and scratches. Since granite is a porous material, seal it regularly to maintain its stain resistance. Its also considered an upgrade, so it adds value to your home. A wide variety of colors and veining are available in granite, making it easy to personalize your look.</p>

8109 </div>

8110 </div>

8111 </div>

8112 </div>

8113 </div>

8114 </div>

8115 </div>

8116 </div>

8117 <div class="Layout-module_omnimerse-column-sm-4__3eiub Layout-module_marginTopOnSmall__2rO47 merce-column">

8118 <div>

8119 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-COLUMN-aeba-ecb-d--eceada">

8120 <div class="merce-column-container">

8121 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-fa-a-b-acf-bbd">

8122 <div>

8123 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

8124 <div>

8125 <p class="subHdr">Marble</p>

8126 </div>

8127 </div>

8128 </div>

8129 </div>

8130 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-SINGLE_IMAGE-ffbb-bef-c-ba-fccca">

8131 <div class="SingleImage-module_singleImage__3fWXf ffbb-bef-c-ba-fccca-singleImageAlignment">

8132 <img title="marble" class="ffbb-bef-c-ba-fccca-image" alt="marble" src="https://img.vevano.com/z5x0pvNaapAGlP-BHO77MhBq_Bp5HJkOIHd83yogFdM/rs:fill:0:132/q:80/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdG9yYWdlLmdvb2dsZWFwaXMuY29tL3ZldmFuby1hc3NldHMvY29zZW50aW5vL2NvdW50ZXJ0b3BNYXJibGUuanBn">

8133 </div>

8134 </div>

8135 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-afe-cd-d--aece">

8136 <div>

8137 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

8138 <div>

8139 <p class="bodyCopy">A gorgeous natural stone, marble is a luxurious add-on that other countertop types often try to mimic. Marble is also a favorite among bakers and chocolatiers given its resistance to temperature changes, so its a good choice for foodies and bakers. Like granite, its a porous material and requires regular sealing to avoid staining. Given that its a luxury, marble not only adds value to a home, but elevates the ambience of your space as well.</p>

8140 </div>

8141 </div>

8142 </div>

8143 </div>

8144 </div>

8145 </div>

8146 </div>

8147 </div>

8148 </div>

8149 </div>

8150 </div>

8151 </div>

8152 </div>

8153 <div>

8154 <div class="styles-plugin-outer custom-outer-style-ROW-fd-c-cf--bca">

8155 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-ROW-fd-c-cf--bca">

8156 <div class="Row-module_global__1T17H merce-row-container">

8157 <div class="Layout-module_row__3IzXF merce-row">

8158 <div class="Layout-module_omnimerse-column-sm-4__3eiub Layout-module_marginTopOnSmall__2rO47 merce-column">

8159 <div>

8160 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-COLUMN-fb-cef-a-bbf-eaec">

8161 <div class="merce-column-container">

8162 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK--c-b-ec-bebb">

8163 <div>

8164 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

8165 <div>

8166 <p class="subHdr">Dekton</p>

8167 </div>

8168 </div>

8169 </div>

8170 </div>

8171 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-SINGLE_IMAGE-abc----a">

8172 <div class="SingleImage-module_singleImage__3fWXf abc----a-singleImageAlignment">

8173 <img title="dekton" class="abc----a-image" alt="dekton" src="https://img.vevano.com/kq6bDroCEd7l_UcmcRP0aCb7icZMs9v6tmBcu0zTXvQ/rs:fill:0:132/q:80/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdG9yYWdlLmdvb2dsZWFwaXMuY29tL3ZldmFuby1hc3NldHMvY29zZW50aW5vL2NvdW50ZXJ0b3BEZWt0b24uanBn">

8174 </div>

8175 </div>

8176 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-bff-cf--ce-abef">

8177 <div>

8178 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

8179 <div>

8180 <p class="bodyCopy">An engineered material, Dekton fuses natural stone, porcelain, and ceramic together through heat and pressure to create a material thats more durable than many stone types. Dekton inherently has high resistance to heat, acids, oils, and freezing temperatures, making it a great option for indoor or outdoor use. Since it is a man-made material, the options for looks and design are varied. Its available in high gloss, matte, or can even look like slate, marble, or wood.</p>

8181 </div>

8182 </div>

8183 </div>

8184 </div>

8185 </div>

8186 </div>

8187 </div>

8188 </div>

8189 <div class="Layout-module_omnimerse-column-sm-4__3eiub Layout-module_marginTopOnSmall__2rO47 merce-column">

8190 <div>

8191 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-COLUMN-fd--a-f-abaac">

8192 <div class="merce-column-container">

8193 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-ac-e--ed-ab">

8194 <div>

8195 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

8196 <div>

8197 <p class="subHdr">Laminate</p>

8198 </div>

8199 </div>

8204 <img title="Laminate" class="eef-a---db-image" alt="Laminate" src="https://img.vevano.com/ndyzbsETNpyuAtrCL9yL2o-iPQNt0ZwkyIVtEC9fmnQ/rs:fill:0:132/q:80/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdG9yYWdlLmdvb2dsZWFwaXMuY29tL3ZldmFuby1hc3NldHMvY29zZW50aW5vL2NvdW50ZXJ0b3BMYW1pbmF0ZS5qcGc">

8209 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

8210 <div>

8211 <p class="bodyCopy">Created from layers of particleboard, resins, plastic, and a photo layer, laminate is a cost-effective option that works well in kitchens. Installation is easy, lighter than stone, with pieces made to order after measuring. Designs are flexible, available in solid colors, stone textures, and others. While not as durable as stone and highly susceptible to heat, it is easy to maintain with soap and water.</p>

8228 <p class="subHdr">Natural Stone</p>

8242 <p class="bodyCopy">Natural stone options include soapstone, limestone, travertine, and others. They are typically resistant to heat, though each type of stone has its own unique properties. Cleaning is easy, consisting of pH neutral soap and water. Natural stone is a great way to add personalization and luxury to a space. Colors, textures, and veining vary, but one thing is for sure: it's beautiful.</p>

With how many styles and types of tile there are, there are endless possibilities when it comes to styling, personalization, and design. Cleaning the tile itself is easy, its the grout lines that require more attention.</p>

While offering quite an array of styles, polishes, and design potential, concrete requires regular upkeep. Wipe up spills immediately, and frequently seal and wax counters to prevent stains and damage.</p>

8345 <p class="bodyCopy">Adding a natural element to any kitchen or bar area, butcher block works especially well with painted cabinets. Use it either sealed or unsealed, though if its sealed its best not to prep food directly on the surface, whereas unsealed can lead to scratched surfaces. Its a cost-effective option compared to stone, but since wood is porous, clean up spills right away to prevent damage.</p>

8405 <h2 class="hdr normal">Caring for Countertops</h2>

8406 <p class="bodyCopy">Each type of countertop material has its own maintenance schedule. Theres regular maintenance, special routines, stain treatments, and possible repairs.</p>

8407 <p class="bodyCopy">As a quick note, most stone countertops are easy to clean with water and a non-abrasive cleanser. Even with stain resistant materials, we recommend cleaning a spill as soon as possible to make sure your counters stay beautiful for years to come.</p>

8408 <p class="bodyCopy">For more information and specifics for each type of stone, see our

8409 <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/care-for-stone-countertops">article on stone maintenance.</a>

8410 </p>

8447 <img title="which countertop is best for kitchens?" class="b-bb---bfdfe-image" alt="which countertop is best for kitchens?" src="https://img.vevano.com/rsFIteMcIpnq-Kf54L3xqiTmCgogIfL04h5RHMAga48/rs:fill:0:132/q:80/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdG9yYWdlLmdvb2dsZWFwaXMuY29tL3ZldmFuby1hc3NldHMvY29zZW50aW5vL2FydGljbGUySW1nTW9iaWxlLmpwZw">

8454 <div>

8455 <h2 class="hdr normal">Which Countertop is Best for Kitchens?</h2>

8456 <p class="bodyCopy">Since kitchens are such high traffic areas in the home, countertop material matters. When considering a countertop for your kitchen, its helpful to prioritize functionality, aesthetics, and budget as each can help guide you on which material and style will best suit your space.</p>

8457 <p class="bodyCopy">Generally speaking, granite, marble, quartz, and solid surfaces such as Dekton are all popular choices for kitchens. Each has a multitude of colors, finishes, and thickness to find the ideal match for your space. Even though Dekton is an engineered stone, there are colors and textures available that look like marble, granite, or quartz, even wood-like styles as well.</p>

8458 <p class="bodyCopy">How this countertop fits in with your daily routine is a major consideration. With butcher block, concrete, and marble, extra care is needed on a regular basis, particularly when it comes to spills. Dekton, granite, tile, and quartz, on the other hand, are more forgiving when it comes to heat, scratches, and spills. Laminate lies somewhere in between. Its resistant to spills and cleans easily, but heat damages laminate quickly.</p>

8459 <p class="bodyCopy">When it comes to cost, butcher block and laminate are the most affordable options, though they dont add to the value of your home. Tile is also a cost-saving option, depending on the style and whether you install it yourself. Stone materials such as quartz, granite, marble add value and tend to last longer than laminate or butcher block, given the natural strength and properties inherent with stone.</p>

8533 <div>

8534 <h2 class="hdr normal">Which Countertop is Best for Bathrooms?</h2>

8535 <p class="bodyCopy">Much like choosing a countertop for your kitchen, choosing one for a bathroom depends on your priorities when it comes to style, function, and budget. With bathrooms, function includes withstanding the variations in humidity and temperature, particularly in bathrooms with showers.</p>

8536 <p class="bodyCopy">For powder rooms, nearly any material works well including butcher block, laminate, stone, and solid surfaces. From there its a matter of what your preferences and needs are as far as style, size, and budget are concerned.</p>

8537 <p class="bodyCopy">For primary bathrooms and larger bathrooms with baths and showers, stone countertops offer long term durability against the varying temperatures and moisture.</p>

8572 </p>

8576 <span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">work with our design team</span>

8577 </a>
